  "prompt": "How do I get Pikachu as my first Pok\u00e9mon in Pok\u00e9mon GO?",
  "response": "In Pok\u00e9mon GO, the typical starter Pok\u00e9mon choices are Bulbasaur, Charmander, and Squirtle. However, there's an easter egg that allows you to choose Pikachu as your starter Pok\u00e9mon. Here\u2019s how you can do it:\n\n1. **Begin the Game:** Start a new game in Pok\u00e9mon GO and go through the initial setup steps, including creating your avatar.\n\n2. **Ignore the Starter Pok\u00e9mon:** When the initial three starter Pok\u00e9mon (Bulbasaur, Charmander, and Squirtle) appear on your map, walk away from them. Physically move away from their location.\n\n3. **Repeat the Process:** As you walk away, the three Pok\u00e9mon will reappear in front of you. Ignore them again and continue walking away. This process needs to be repeated four times.\n\n4. **Pikachu Appears:** After the fourth time, Pikachu will eventually appear alongside the original three starter Pok\u00e9mon.\n\n5. **Catch Pikachu:** Tap on Pikachu and catch it just like you would any other Pok\u00e9mon. Congratulations, you've now chosen Pikachu as your starter Pok\u00e9mon!\n\nThis method works due to the game\u2019s design and allows you to start with Pikachu instead of the other starter Pok\u00e9mon. Enjoy your journey in Pok\u00e9mon GO!",
